abstract: Paying attention to the impeachment trial this week? Us too. But here are 7 things that happened on the campaign trail you may have missed.
snippet: Paying attention to the impeachment trial this week? Us too. But here are 7 things that happened on the campaign trail you may have missed.
lead_paragraph: The Iowa caucuses are just around the corner — but with the impeachment trial underway in Washington, the presidential campaign is in a strange sort of suspended animation.

abstract: A regular mixer brings together designers and typography nerds who get consumed by spacing and serifs.
snippet: A regular mixer brings together designers and typography nerds who get consumed by spacing and serifs.
lead_paragraph: At TypeThursday, a monthly meet-up in cities including Los Angeles; London; and Bucharest, Romania, font designers critique each other’s letterforms over wine. They hold forth about negative space, consistent strokes and serif experimentation. The group’s website bills the gathering as “three hours of fontastic fun.”

abstract: A new study, which found that Americans were reluctant to use the word “she” to describe a hypothetical president, highlights the sneaky ways language illuminates bias.
snippet: A new study, which found that Americans were reluctant to use the word “she” to describe a hypothetical president, highlights the sneaky ways language illuminates bias.
lead_paragraph: It was a blip of a moment during the Democratic debate last week, one perhaps overshadowed by a long discussion of the prospect of a female president. Responding to a question about climate change, Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts said, “I will do everything a president can do all by herself on the first day.”

abstract: The move, which would be unlikely to happen until after the Senate impeachment trial, could enhance her chances of becoming vice president but could also anger liberals in California.
snippet: The move, which would be unlikely to happen until after the Senate impeachment trial, could enhance her chances of becoming vice president but could also anger liberals in California.
lead_paragraph: Senator Kamala Harris is weighing an endorsement of Joseph R. Biden Jr., according to multiple Democratic officials familiar with her deliberations. Such a move could lift Mr. Biden’s campaign and perhaps do even more to enhance Ms. Harris’s chances of becoming vice president, but it could also anger her liberal base in California.

abstract: Telling someone you don’t want to be friends anymore can be awkward. So don’t tell them.
snippet: Telling someone you don’t want to be friends anymore can be awkward. So don’t tell them.
lead_paragraph: The rules for breaking up with a partner have long been established: Try to do it in person or at least on the phone, don’t do it over a text message or a Post-it note. Ending a friendship? That’s complicated.
